column1: #Text=Mutebi Nnyonyintono Kiweewa was Kabaka of the Kingdom of Buganda from 2 August 1888 until 21 October 1888 .
#Text=He was born at Nakatema prior to 1856 , the eldest son of Kabaka Mukaabya Walugembe Mutesa I Kayiira , Kabaka of Buganda , who reigned between 1856 and 1884 .
#Text=His mother was Kiribakka of the Mamba clan .
#Text=He ascended to the throne following the defeat of his younger brother , Kabaka Mwanga II by the combined Christian , Muslim and rebel Baganda forces .
#Text=The defeat of Mwanga II occurred on 2 August 1888 .
#Text=He maintained his capital at Mengo Hill . [ 1 ]
#Text=He is recorded to have married twenty ( 20 ) wives : [ 2 ]
#Text=Naabakyaala Zandaba , the Namasole , previously the Kaddulubaale
#Text=He fathered 23 children , 21 sons and two daughters :
#Text=Prince Kiweewa Ssimbwa , whose mother was Lady Butema
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Walulyo I , whose mother was Lady Butema
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Kibuuka , whose mother was Lady Kajja
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Muyinda , whose mother was Lady Luleba , Omusenero
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Agustin [ Gusito ] Tebandeke , whose mother was Lady Namubiru .
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Lulaba , whose mother was Lady Namuli
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Kagunya , whose mother was Lady Namuli
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Lukongwa , the Ssaabalangira ( Chief Prince ) , whose mother was Lady Namusoke
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Kiwanuka , whose mother was Lady Namusoke
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Walulyo II , whose mother was Lady Namusoke
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Kalubagwiire , whose mother was Lady Nambajjwe
#Text=Sekamaanya , whose mother was Lady Nambi I
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Namulinzi I , whose mother was Lady Nambi II
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Mwanga , whose mother was Lady Nambi III
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Chwa , whose mother was Tebalyayeebwa
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Ngenza , whose mother was Tebalyayeebwa
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Namulinzi II , whose mother was Teyansigira
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Namika , whose mother was Lady Lwandeeta
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Musisi , whose mother was Lwandeeta
#Text=Prince ( Omulangira ) Nasuswa , whose mother was Lady Zandaba
#Text=Princess ( Omumbejja ) Agaati Kagere , whose mother Tebalyayeebwa
#Text=Kabaka Kiweewa Nnyonyintono 's rein is the shortest in the recorded history of Buganda .
#Text=He was the Kabaka-in-waiting for around six weeks ; after he was crowned , he lasted a mere forty days on the throne .

#Text=His reign was characterized by conflict and rebellion among the members of the royal court and intrigue and plotting among the Arabic Muslim and European Christian forces that supported the warring factions .
#Text=He was deposed by the Muslim forces of his brother Kabaka Kalema Muguluma , who reigned from 21 October 1888 until 5 October 1889 .
#Text=He was captured and thrown in jail .
#Text=He was killed in prison by his Muslim captors in July 1889 .
